The paper discusses techniques for improving search efficiency in planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on partial order based reduction (POR) in planning, which is a technique for reducing the size of the search space. This connects to the subfield of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL), which often involves optimizing code and reducing the size of the search space. The paper also discusses the stubborn set theory in model checking, which is a subfield of logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for POR, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
